HEADWORD: Kodiak bear
<hw>Kodiak bear</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large brown bear (<spn>Ursus
middendorffi</spn> syn. <spn>Ursus arctos</spn>
<varn>middendorffi</varn>) of coastal Alaska and British Columbia
related to the grizzly bear; called also <altname>Kodiak
bear</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Alaskan brown bear, Kodiak, <spn>Ursus
middendorffi</spn>, <spn>Ursus arctos</spn>
<varn>middendorffi</varn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
